29/06/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn said on Wednesday (28 June) that Bulgaria and Romania have made significant progress in their EU accession reforms, and voiced optimism that the two candidates could recover from delays in the process and join the Union in January. Rehn was speaking at the opening of a two-day regional business and investment summit on Bulgaria, Greece and Romania, organised by The Economist magazine in Athens. (Naftemporiki - 29/06/06; Darik, ANA - 28/06/06)
